
This is a binary file that would normally be downloaded during Gradle wrapper setup. For a production setup, you would run:
gradle wrapper --gradle-version 8.0

This would generate the actual gradle-wrapper.jar file. Since this is a text-based system, you'll need to either:
1. Run the gradle wrapper command after setting up the project
2. Copy the gradle-wrapper.jar from an existing Android project
3. Download it from the Gradle distribution

The file should be approximately 60KB in size and is a standard JAR file containing the Gradle wrapper classes.
